<TITLE> 4 seriously hurt in CNG blast </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Mar 16 (bdnews24.com)  At least four people were injured severely after a gas cylinder exploded at a CNG station at Uttara's Abdullapur area in the capital on Tuesday. The injured were admitted to Dhaka Medical College Hospital's burn unit. Uttara police chief Khandaker Rezaul Hassan told bdnews24.com that the cylinder exploded when the four people were working in a compressor room at Tasin CNG Filling Station at around 7am. The condition of the injured workers is critical, he said. They could not be identified at this time, the official added. b
